OL,3,CMore than 200 pubs closed in six
OL,4,Cmonths amid tax hikes, figures show
OL,6,FAt the same time, the Government
OL,7,Fincreased the rate of employer
OL,8,Fnational insurance contributions from
OL,9,F13.8% to 15% and also lowered the
OL,10,Fthreshold at which firms would pay the
OL,11,Ftax.
OL,13,FMany pubs were also hit by changes to
OL,14,Fdiscounts on business rates, the
OL,15,Fproperty tax affecting high street
OL,16,Fbusinesses.
OL,18,FHospitality businesses received a 60%
OL,19,Fdiscount on their business rates bills
OL,20,Fup to a cap of #110,000 but saw this
OL,21,Fcut to only 25% in April.
